This project is a simple web-based E-Library system developed to manage digital book information. The application uses a Node.js backend and a MySQL database to store and retrieve data related to books.
The project demonstrates how a backend server can connect with a database and provide a basic system for managing library records.

Technologies Used
- Node.js
- MySQL
- JavaScript
- HTML
- CSS

Features
- Store book information in a database
- Retrieve book data from MySQL
- Backend server built using Node.js
- Basic web interface for interacting with the system

Project Structure
- Backend server developed using Node.js
- Database connection using MySQL
- Project dependencies managed with Node packages

Purpose of the Project
The purpose of this project is to understand how web applications interact with databases and how Node.js can be used to build backend services.

Future Improvements
- Add user login system
- Add book search functionality
- Implement book borrowing and return management
